"n.大洪水；暴雨 【英】 n. 大洪水 (a great flood)；暴雨 (a heavy rainfall) 【考】 deluge : droplet / landslide : pebble(暴雨对小雨滴/山崩 对小卵石)barrage : explosives / deluge : rain(大量的炮弹形成弹幕 /大量的下雨形成暴雨)rain : deluge / wind : hurricane(雨和暴雨/风和暴风)反义词：drizzle(细 雨) 【记】 de+luge(=luv冲洗)→ 冲掉→大洪水 【同】 参考：deluvial(大洪 水的); dilute(冲淡) n. 大洪水; 暴雨 【记】de向下, luge = luv冲洗一倾盆大雨发音特殊: 中间有一个""quot;流""quot;－大洪水大人总是delude小孩: deluge来了! 【参】dilute(v 冲淡; 稀释; adj 淡的; 稀释的) 【类】deluge: droplet = landslide: pebble 暴雨对小雨滴 = 山崩石对小卵石barrage: explosives = deluge: rain大量炮弹形成弹幕 = 大量下雨形成暴雨rain: deluge = wind: hurricane 雨对暴雨 = 风对飓风 【反】drizzle(n 细雨) 【记】de加强 + luge (luv 冲洗)→冲掉→大洪水；音：地流汁，地上流水汁 【相关】deluvial 大洪水的， dilute 冲淡 deluge (n.)  late 14c., from Old French deluge (12c.), earlier deluve, from Latin diluvium ""flood, inundation,"" from diluere ""wash away,"" from dis- ""away"" (see dis-) + -luere, comb. form of lavere ""to wash"" (see lave). deluge (v.)  1590s; see deluge (n.). Related: Deluged; deluging."
